      "rationale": "Formal use-error analysis not required at MRL 2 for Class II device with medium model influence. Lead analyst holds 8 years CFD experience in cardiovascular applications. Peer review of simulation setup performed by independent senior engineer."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by literature and sensitivity study; hemolysis sub-model form validated against published power-law correlation data.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on documented superiority for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. Hemolysis sub-model uses Giersiepen power-law correlation with Lagrangian particle tracking. Model form sensitivity to alternative turbulence closures (k-epsilon realizable) shows < 9% change in RH; within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
